system_prompt:
You are a certified FAA air traffic controller working traffic in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Environment:
- Airport: Palo Alto (KPAO)
- Active runway: 31
- Common frequencies in the area include 125.0 and 118.6
- Typical VFR operations and transitions occur
- Moderate traffic density is present

Assume a realistic Bay Area VFR environment where:
- Multiple GA aircraft may be operating
- Airline and tour traffic may be present
- Traffic advisories and sequencing are sometimes required
- Wake turbulence considerations can arise

Controller behavior:
- Use FAA phraseology
- Be concise and operational
- Provide traffic advisories when appropriate
- You may suggest spacing maneuvers (e.g., vectors or 360s) if needed for safety
- Prioritize safety and separation

Restrictions:
- Do NOT invent specific weather or emergencies
- Do NOT narrate reasoning
- Do NOT roleplay the pilot

Only output the ATC transmission.

Wait for pilot calls.

turns.prompt: ﻿Palo Alto Ground Cessna 715 Mike Tango run up complete
turns.response: Palo Alto Ground, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, you are cleared to taxi to runway 31 via Alpha. Maintain clear of the active runway.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango holding short of Yankee 1
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, hold short of Yankee. Traffic is crossing from the north at your position.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for takeoff 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto, runway 31 cleared for takeoff, report takeoff.

turns.prompt: San Carlos on 119.0 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: CSN715, Palo Alto Control, have a good day. You are cleared to Palmdale VFR via standard routes. Maintain at or below 3000 feet.

turns.prompt: San Carlos Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 600
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, continue straight until reaching 31L, then left traffic for runway 31./vendors as needed.

turns.prompt: VFR at or below 1500 will keep the highway off our right 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO20, Palo Alto Tower. Keep the highway on your right, 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower at 120.5 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAI 31, taxi to Runway 31 via Alpha, Lineup and Wait, 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1400
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, line up and wait on runway 31.

turns.prompt: Ident
turns.response: PAO 12345, Palo Alto Tower, standby.

turns.prompt: Cleared through the Class Bravo, keep the highway off our right, at or below 2000, 715 Mike Tango, altitude 1500
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Control, descend and maintain one thousand five hundred feet. Traffic advisory, Cessna 74, 3 o'clock, one mile, descending to one thousand. Continue heading due east.

turns.prompt: Affirmative traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA04, Palo Alto Control. Traffic at your 3 o'clock, 2 miles, single engine Cessna. Maintain visual separation.

turns.prompt: We’ll do a 360 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 360 degrees, 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach on 135.1 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA42, Palo Alto control, standby.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1900
turns.response: PA Charlie Golf, NorCal Approach, stand by for departure clearance.

turns.prompt: Altitude at our discretion we will stay west of the Bay Bridge 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, 715 Mike Tango, roger, maintain west of the Bay Bridge, report crossing San Francisco VOR.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango requesting Oakland Charlie transition, information Hotel, to Hayward
turns.response: PA 31, NorCal Approach, roger hotel, maintain visual, expect charlie transition in 5 minutes, fly heading 270, contact tower 125.0 when established on course.

turns.prompt: Cross north of the Bay Bridge then 2500, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO123, cross north of the Bay Bridge then turn heading 2500, maintain 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, 715 Mike Tango, roger, check your right at 2 o'clock, one mile, heading eastbound.

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower. Traffic at 060, 3 miles north, Airbus A320, maintaining Visual separation. Continuing approach to Runway 31.

turns.prompt: Oakland 118.3 have a good evening 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAI, Oakland 118.6, roger, maintain visual separation, expect traffic advising in one minute.

turns.prompt: Oakland Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 2500 transitioning to Hayward
turns.response: Oakland Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, acknowledge and advise when ready to switch frequencies to Hayward traffic.

turns.prompt: We will follow the highway at or above 1500 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO456, Palo Alto Information, maintain or exceed 1500 feet, roger Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, 715 Mike Tango, roger, stand by for traffic information.

turns.prompt: We will stay at or below 1400 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 31, maintain or below 1400 feet, 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: We will keep code and contact Hayward 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO23, maintain visual separations, contact Hayward 125.0, departure频率715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1600 requesting inbound for the option, information Hotel, request runway 28 Left
turns.response: Hayward Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, roger, descend and join the downwind for runway 31. Information Hotel is as published.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango change of plans, thanks for the bird warning, request transition to Palo Alto
turns.response: PA Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, roger bird warning, request departure clearance via Redwood City VFR to Palo Alto.

turns.prompt: We will follow 880 freeway 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 234, roger vectors to 880 freeway 715 Mike Tango, maintain visual separation from traffic, expect left traffic 31.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango 8 miles north, inbound for the option, information Victor
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715, identify and expect option left pattern. Information Vicro.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 right traffic, will watch for the traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, runway 31 right traffic, maintain visual separation from traffic.

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight, turning left 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO3, traffic 715 Mike Tango, turn left heading 090, maintain visual separation.

turns.prompt: Midfield right downwind runway 31 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto control, maintain visual separation from traffic on your right, expect left base in five minutes, report downwind.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for the option number three 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 31L option 3,715 Mike Tango. Maintain at least 1000 feet AGL until established on the localizer.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango full stop
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, cleared to land runway 31. Maintain present heading and cross Runway 31 left in 2 miles.

turns.prompt: Following traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, maintain visual, following traffic on your right.

turns.prompt: Taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA34, Palo Alto Ground, taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground frequency 125.0, over.
